Presidential candidate, Nelson Chamisa, is calling for more to be done to ensure elections due to be held this year is free, fair and credible. He is also meeting with Zimbabwean expatriates in a bid to lure them back home to help rebuild Zimbabwe’s economy. 

Chamisa also hopes to discuss the vote due later this year, and for the future of Zimbabwe. 

